We are now ready to define the reduced realization space of a matroid. 

\begin{defin}[Reduced realization space]\label{reducedrealizationspace}
 For a rank $d$ matroid $M$ with ground set $E=\{1,\ldots,m\}$ and 
 $\{1,\ldots,d\}$ as basis, the \emph{reduced realization space} of $M$ 
over~$\mathbb{C}$ is the set~$\mathcal{R}_{\mathbb{C}}^{R}(M)$ of matrices 
$A\in M_{d,m}(\mathbb{C})$ that satisfy the following 
 conditions:

 \begin{itemize}
  \item[(C1)] $A$ realizes $M$ over $\mathbb{C}$, i.e., $A$ belongs to 
$\mathcal{R}_{\mathbb{C}}(M)$;
  \item[(C2)] $A$ is of the form $\left(I_{d}\left|{\widetilde}{A}\right.\right)$, 
where $I_d$ is the $d \times d$ identity matrix;
  \item[(C3)] the entries of ${\widetilde}{A}$ that are in the normal frame 
$\mathcal{P}_{{\widetilde}{A}}$ equal $1$. 
 \end{itemize}

 We endow~$\mathcal{R}_{\mathbb{C}}^{R}(M)$ with the subspace topology 
of~$M_{d,m}(\mathbb{C})$.
\end{defin}

